Hi!
My team has recently received the REV starter bot kit of parts. Has anyone else receive wrong parts. Specifically the gears. We are trying to put the gears on our brand new NEO motors but they are loose on them. Does anyone know what we should do or if anyone is facing a similar problem?

We found that the shafts of the NEOs we purchased this year were undersized. Pinion gears that should’ve been press fit were slip fit.

@PatrickW reccomended that we use Loctite Retaining Compound on the pinions.

SDS Mk4 with Neos

The press fit issue issue is caused by the slightly smaller shaft diameter of recent NEO motors. Unfortunately all vendors’ press-fit pinions do not press fit on these shafts. Please use Loctite 609 or 638 retaining compound to permanently bond the pinion to the motor shaft. This is a proven method of attaching slip-fit pinions to motor shafts. Be careful to not get any retaining compound in the motor’s bearing.

motor shaft through the thin plastic all the way down to the bearing to prevent any retaining compound getting on there is a good option then just rip/cut the plastic off later.
